This project focuses on predicting whether borrowers will successfully repay their loans using the LendingClub dataset through the implementation of two machine learning techniques: Decision Tree and Random Forest. The dataset was examined by analyzing important factors such as FICO scores, interest rates, and loan purposes, while categorical features were transformed into numerical values to prepare the data for model training. A Random Forest model consisting of 600 trees was developed and evaluated against a single Decision Tree model using confusion matrices and classification reports. The findings indicated that the Random Forest model outperformed the Decision Tree, achieving an accuracy of approximately 85%, though both models experienced challenges in predicting the minority class because of class imbalance in the dataset.
